1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,627
[Mustapha] <i>The police found out</i>

2
00:00:02,711 --> 00:00:05,964
<i>that the ship was carrying</i>
<i>illegal firearms.</i>

3
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:07,674
[Mustapha]
<i>When they were about to capture it,</i>

4
00:00:07,757 --> 00:00:08,925
the ship exploded.

5
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:12,470
Now tell me that the ship
wasn't deliberately

6
00:00:12,554 --> 00:00:14,055
<i>detonated to make it sink.</i>

7
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:16,808
[Teresa]
<i>They're the ones behind the tragedy</i>

8
00:00:16,891 --> 00:00:18,435
<i>that killed Gabriel.</i>

9
00:00:18,518 --> 00:00:19,686
[Teresa] <i>And until now…</i>

10
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:21,563
<i>They're still running free.</i>

11
00:00:21,646 --> 00:00:25,608
<i>I've been grieving for my son</i>
<i>for decades, Jamilah.</i>

12
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:28,778
But you're certain
that it was not an accident?

13
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:30,071
Why do you ask?

14
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:31,614
My brother died because of that explosion.

15
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,200
What happened to that ship
was not an accident.

16
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:37,704
MV Emilia was intentionally blown up.

17
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:40,331
[Manuel] <i>Mustapha knows.</i>

18
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:42,667
<i>We have to get rid of him!</i>

19
00:00:42,751 --> 00:00:45,128
[man] <i>Copy, General. Everything is ready.</i>

20
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:49,174
[Jalil] <i>Someone's tailing Sir Mustapha.</i>

21
00:00:49,257 --> 00:00:50,467
His life is in danger.

22
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:52,552
[Jalil] <i>Sir, someone is following you.</i>

23
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:54,637
- [Mustapha] <i>They don't seem hostile.</i>
- [explosion]

24
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:59,601
- [motorcycle revving]
- [gunshots]

25
00:00:59,684 --> 00:01:01,102
[tires screeching]

26
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:03,146
[Datu Rahman] <i>Jalil is risking his life.</i>

27
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:04,105
What's your plan?

28
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:07,609
I'll tell him the truth, Omar.
Even if it's hard.

29
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:08,526
- [tires screech]
- [explosion]

30
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,320
[Mustapha in Arabic] <i>Praise be to God.</i>

31
00:01:11,988 --> 00:01:17,911
[rapid gunfire]

32
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:21,956
[Mustapha] <i>I'm grateful you guys came.</i>

33
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,291
[in Arabic] <i>Praise be to God.</i>

34
00:01:23,374 --> 00:01:24,918
I need to talk to the president.

35
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:27,253
I'll make sure to settle everything.

36
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:30,048
We need to put an end
to Carillo's evil schemes.

37
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:32,175
[man] <i>General, awaiting your order, sir.</i>

38
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:35,303
Execute.

39
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:40,141
[whirring]

40
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:41,601
- [missile roars]
- [explosion]

41
00:01:41,684 --> 00:01:42,936
Sir Mustapha!

42
00:01:48,608 --> 00:01:55,156
[theme music playing]

43
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:09,838
[system beeping]

44
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,047
[Manuel groans]

45
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:15,802
- [morose music playing]
- [system beeping]

46
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:19,556
[breathes deeply]

47
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:21,266
Goodbye…

48
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,643
Ahmad Mustapha.

49
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:27,981
You are a worthy opponent.

50
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:32,777
And as for you,

51
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:36,865
Reyes and Espina…

52
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:40,743
now that Mustapha is gone,

53
00:02:41,744 --> 00:02:44,914
it'll be much easier for me to defeat you…

54
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:51,462
and carry out my plans.

55
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:55,508
[sinister laughter]

56
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:03,474
[reporter] <i>Presidential Chief</i>
<i>of Staff Ahmad Mustapha</i>

57
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:06,811
<i>was killed after he and his</i>
<i>security escort were ambushed</i>

58
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:09,063
<i>by unidentified armed men.</i>

59
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:11,149
<i>According to the initial report,</i>

60
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:14,694
<i>his vehicle was blown up</i>
<i>by drone missiles.</i>

61
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:17,697
<i>The attack happened just hours</i>

62
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:21,451
<i>after his live interview</i>
<i>on Maya Mae Kalaw's program.</i>

63
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:22,744
We're now joined

64
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:26,080
by Task Force Alpha Agent Marcus Reyes.

65
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:27,123
Sir, what happened?

66
00:03:28,124 --> 00:03:29,751
It is with deep regret that we announce

67
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:35,673
Presidential Chief of Staff
Ahmad Mustapha was ambushed

68
00:03:36,257 --> 00:03:39,344
<i>because he was getting close</i>
<i>to uncovering the people behind</i>

69
00:03:39,427 --> 00:03:42,055
<i>the destabilization of our government.</i>

70
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:44,390
[reporter] <i>Who was behind it?</i>

71
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:46,976
We already have a suspect.

72
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:50,021
<i>But for now, we can't reveal any names</i>

73
00:03:50,104 --> 00:03:51,981
<i>because our investigation</i>
<i>is still ongoing.</i>

74
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:55,401
[tense music playing]

75
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,070
<i>You know who you are.</i>

76
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,406
You'd better hide,

77
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:05,036
because we won't stop
until you're rotting in prison.

78
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:08,206
PRESIDENTIAL CHIEF OF STAFF
AHMAD MUSTAPHA DEAD

79
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:10,541
Reyes!

80
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:14,545
What did Ahmad Mustapha tell you?!

81
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:16,965
What do you know?!

82
00:04:18,716 --> 00:04:19,717
General…

83
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:23,721
I believe Espina and Marcus
are working together.

84
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:25,598
They're the ones ruining our plans.

85
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:28,768
I strongly suspect Allan Espina.

86
00:04:28,851 --> 00:04:32,647
Mustapha was the one
who put him in the NLEA and the SID!

87
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:36,150
Find out what he knows.

88
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:38,861
[tense music continues]

89
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:40,780
We're so close to succeeding,

90
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:44,075
so we have to eliminate anyone
who could ruin our plans!

91
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:54,502
Son, don't blame yourself
for what happened.

92
00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:57,338
There were too many of them,
and they were heavily armed.

93
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,549
You and Allan never stood a chance.

94
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:01,676
I know that, Ma.

95
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:04,637
[sighs]
I just can't get it out of my head.

96
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:06,306
We were so close to him.

97
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:09,183
He was right there in front of us.

98
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:11,728
I really thought we'd won

99
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:13,813
and that Sir Mustapha
was finally going to make it.

100
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:17,275
Then suddenly…

101
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:19,527
- [missile roars]
- [explosion]

102
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:20,987
[both groaning]

103
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,031
And besides that…

104
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,285
I thought I was finally going to find out

105
00:05:27,368 --> 00:05:30,413
who was behind the bombing
of the MV Doña Emilia.

106
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,502
That's the reason Gabriel died.

107
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:41,257
[glum music playing]

108
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:43,843
But then, they killed Sir Mustapha.

109
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:52,560
[Jamilah breathing heavily]

110
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,687
[Jamilah] I feel so bad for Sir Mustapha.

111
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:55,813
[exhales]

112
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:59,734
He gave his life
trying to uncover the truth.

113
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,362
[breathes deeply] Father…

114
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:07,950
[sobbing]

115
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:10,745
I tried to stop the explosion.

116
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:12,955
But I failed.

117
00:06:14,582 --> 00:06:16,501
What do you mean, Father?

118
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:19,504
What Sir Mustapha said

119
00:06:20,421 --> 00:06:23,299
about the explosion at the MV Doña Emilia,

120
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:26,260
I know all about it because I was there.

121
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:28,096
I was involved.

122
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:29,138
What?!

123
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:33,851
The major was going to blow up the boat

124
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:38,314
to destroy all the evidence
against the syndicate.

125
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,818
So I went there.

126
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:44,112
To defuse the bombs.

127
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:49,283
To spare the lives
of those innocent passengers.

128
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:50,576
The police have gotten wind

129
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,495
that there's a hidden shipment
of weapons here.

130
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,580
They're just waiting
for the ship to dock at the pier.

131
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,249
The major planted a bomb here

132
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:58,334
to erase all the evidence
that could point to him.

133
00:06:58,417 --> 00:07:00,711
That bastard! Argh!

134
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:02,839
So many innocent people will die!

135
00:07:02,922 --> 00:07:03,798
Including my family!

136
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,508
We need to find the bomb

137
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,845
so we can defuse it
and save all the people here!

138
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,138
[Gabriel crying]

139
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:11,848
[young Marcus] Gabriel! Let's go!

140
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:13,015
[passengers shouting]

141
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:16,644
[Datu Rahman] <i>I did everything I could.</i>

142
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:19,480
But I failed.

143
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,567
The truth is…

144
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:29,740
that's how I found your brother, Jalil.

145
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:32,577
What do you mean?

146
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:36,080
- [young Datu Rahman] <i>Victor!</i>
- [Victor] <i>Hassan…</i>

147
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,124
[gasping] My children…

148
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:42,420
P-Please save them… Save them…

149
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:43,796
[gasping]

150
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:49,719
He was the son of my friend Victor.

151
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:55,224
He and I tried
to stop the ship from exploding.

152
00:07:56,058 --> 00:08:00,855
Because his family was aboard.

153
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:03,524
But Victor was killed.

154
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:06,819
I was only able to save Jalil.

155
00:08:06,903 --> 00:08:09,447
[morose music playing]

156
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:12,074
I didn't know his family.

157
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:16,746
I didn't know where they lived.

158
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,873
There was no way to find them.

159
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:24,670
I don't even know if they survived.

160
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:29,634
Allan…

161
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:34,805
I have a feeling he's Gabriel,
my missing son.

162
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,057
[sniffles]

163
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,266
Father.

164
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,352
Yes.

165
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:41,812
Yes, my child.

166
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:47,902
I'm going to tell Jalil the truth.

167
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:50,404
[sniffles]

168
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:54,659
But I need to tell him in person.

169
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:06,963
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil,</i>

170
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:11,259
<i>are you Doctor Teresa's missing son?</i>

171
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:14,303
<i>Are you…</i>

172
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:16,472
<i>Gabriel?</i>

173
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:21,769
[morose music continues]

174
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:28,109
[pensive music playing]

175
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:30,194
[rapid gunfire]

176
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:31,988
[Jalil in Arabic]
<i>I seek refuge in Allah from Satan,</i>

177
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:33,447
<i>the expelled from His mercy.</i>

178
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:34,782
<i>In the name of Allah,</i>

179
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:37,326
the Entirely Merciful,
the Especially Merciful.

180
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:40,788
<i>All praise is due to Allah,</i>
<i>Lord of the worlds.</i>

181
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:43,624
<i>The Entirely Merciful,</i>
<i>the Especially Merciful.</i>

182
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,585
<i>Sovereign of the Day of Recompense.</i>

183
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:50,464
It is You we worship
and You we ask for help.

184
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:55,094
Guide us to the straight path.

185
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,598
The path of those upon
whom You have bestowed favor…

186
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:03,144
<i>not of those who have earned Your anger</i>

187
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:06,230
<i>or of those who are astray.</i>

188
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:10,693
[pensive music continues]

189
00:10:20,077 --> 00:10:24,498
[imam 1 in Maranao] <i>We gather in prayer</i>

190
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,334
<i>for Ahmad Mustapha,</i>

191
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:29,962
<i>who served his nation</i>

192
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:33,841
<i>with courage and duty.</i>

193
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:37,386
[imam 2 in Maguidanaon] <i>We ask Allah</i>

194
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:41,057
<i>have mercy upon him, grant him peace,</i>

195
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:46,687
<i>and comfort his family</i>
<i>and all who mourn him.</i>

196
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:50,650
[imam 3 in Tausug]
<i>Indeed, to Allah we belong</i>

197
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:54,153
<i>and to Him we return.</i>

198
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:56,072
[imam 4 in Arabic]
<i>Allah, forgive our brother</i>

199
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,657
<i>Ahmad Mustapha,</i>

200
00:10:57,740 --> 00:11:00,409
<i>have mercy upon him,</i>
<i>grant him peace, and pardon him.</i>

201
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:01,994
<i>Honor his place in the Hereafter</i>

202
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,954
<i>and widen his entrance.</i>

203
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:08,376
<i>He has departed from us,</i>

204
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:13,422
<i>and only his good name and deeds remain.</i>

205
00:11:13,506 --> 00:11:17,760
<i>Reward him with goodness</i>
<i>and admit him into Paradise</i>

206
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:19,178
<i>through Your mercy.</i>

207
00:11:19,261 --> 00:11:20,096
<i>O Allah, accept our prayer.</i>

208
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:24,850
[rapid gunfire]

209
00:11:26,894 --> 00:11:29,688
- [missile roars]
- [explosion]

210
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:34,110
[somber music playing]

211
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:42,243
[morose music playing]

212
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:57,091
[cameras clicking]

213
00:11:57,174 --> 00:12:02,596
[morose music continues]

214
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:11,647
[cameras clicking]

215
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,690
[exhales]

216
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:19,905
Today, the nation lost one of its sons.

217
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:25,828
Ahmad Mustapha was
not only my Chief of Staff,

218
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:27,663
he was also my friend.

219
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:31,459
A man I considered a brother.

220
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:33,169
Even back in college,

221
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:37,381
we dreamed of building
a better Philippines together.

222
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:41,886
A dream he never abandoned.

223
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:49,018
Ahmad Mustapha was a proud Muslim.

224
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:53,355
And also a devoted public servant

225
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:58,986
who dedicated his life
to proving that our diversity

226
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:00,321
is our strength.

227
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:05,993
And that our faith should unite us

228
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:07,244
and never divide us.

229
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:12,750
He served this country with honor

230
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:16,504
until his very last breath.

231
00:13:20,132 --> 00:13:23,385
So whoever's behind this crime…

232
00:13:24,803 --> 00:13:26,138
I assure you…

233
00:13:27,014 --> 00:13:31,018
you will be found,
and justice will be served.

234
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:33,145
[shutters clicking]

235
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:36,941
If you think you've silenced Mustapha,

236
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:38,609
you're mistaken.

237
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:44,865
Because his voice lives on
through the people he inspired.

238
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:50,829
And his legacy lives on
in the nation he helped build.

239
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:57,044
May Allah grant Ahmad Mustapha

240
00:13:57,127 --> 00:14:01,048
eternal peace,
and may God bless our republic.

241
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:08,556
[dramatic music playing]

242
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:12,768
[shutters clicking]

243
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:23,237
<i>In solidarity with the nation's mourning,</i>

244
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:25,322
<i>especially the Muslim community,</i>

245
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:27,741
<i>over the passing of Ahmad Mustapha,</i>

246
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:30,160
<i>President Natalia Mendoza held a memorial</i>

247
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:32,037
<i>for her former Chief of Staff.</i>

248
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:32,997
PRES. NATALIA MENDOZA HOLDS MEMORIAL
FOR FORMER CHIEF OF STAFF AHMAD MUSTAPHA

249
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:35,708
[shutters clicking]

250
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:39,920
[dramatic music continues]

251
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:41,297
[Manuel] Madam President.

252
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:44,258
General Carillo.

253
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:46,719
[exhales] Don't worry.

254
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:49,305
I will get to the bottom of this.

255
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:53,559
[exhales] I'll find out who killed Ahmad.

256
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:55,519
Why he was killed,

257
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:59,356
and what their real plan
against the government is.

258
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:02,651
Thank you.

259
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,486
Now that Ahmad's gone,

260
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,739
I'll need your help more than ever.

261
00:15:07,948 --> 00:15:10,451
You can count on me, Madam President.

262
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:20,461
[stirring music playing]

263
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:23,797
[music stops]

264
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:31,555
[pensive music playing]

265
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,393
There. I fixed it.

266
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:37,519
Yay!

267
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,063
Idol!

268
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:41,482
You're amazing, Marcus!

269
00:15:41,565 --> 00:15:43,275
I love you!

270
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:46,070
I love you too, Gabriel.

271
00:15:47,154 --> 00:15:48,405
[young Marcus] <i>Gabriel, don't let go!</i>

272
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:50,866
- Just hang on!
- Marcus!

273
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,118
- Marcus!
- Gabriel!

274
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:56,914
What happened on that ship
wasn't an accident.

275
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:01,377
The MV Emilia was bombed.

276
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:09,218
[pensive music continues]

277
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:13,263
[knocks]

278
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:15,975
[Jalil] Bro.

279
00:16:19,436 --> 00:16:20,396
How have you been?

280
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:26,360
I'm okay.

281
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:30,364
What's that?

282
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,033
[exhales deeply]

283
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:36,120
It belonged to my little brother.

284
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:38,455
It was his favorite toy.

285
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:42,001
I carry it with me everywhere.

286
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:43,711
Even on missions.

287
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:47,047
It's like a good luck charm.

288
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:48,173
[chuckles]

289
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:54,013
It reminds me why, and who,
I'm fighting for.

290
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:00,519
[Marcus sighs]

291
00:17:00,602 --> 00:17:02,187
What's wrong?

292
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:05,190
When Sir Mustapha died…

293
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:07,651
the whole truth died with him.

294
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,448
Back then, I felt like I was
letting Gabriel down.

295
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:13,323
Bro…

296
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:16,535
As long as our enemies keep beating us,

297
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:20,706
I feel like I'm failing Gabriel even more.

298
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:25,377
Bro, that's not true.

299
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:29,882
We'll get justice for your brother.

300
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:32,051
And we'll put an end to all of this.

301
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:35,304
[morose music playing]

302
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:36,305
[pats]

303
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:41,560
[thuds]

304
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:44,938
Close that door!

305
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:50,652
[thuds]

306
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:51,612
Goddamn it!

307
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,615
You bastard, Carillo!

308
00:17:54,698 --> 00:17:55,783
Bastard!

309
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:59,661
We need to bring General Carillo down.

310
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:01,997
But how?

311
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,916
His influence reaches everywhere,

312
00:18:03,999 --> 00:18:05,918
and he's always surrounded by his men.

313
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:08,962
Then let's go after his accomplices.

314
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:11,173
Weaken him first.

315
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,637
I've already put together
a conspiracy board.

316
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,019
[tapping on screen]

317
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:29,399
There are people that Director Azuelo
and I are suspicious of,

318
00:18:30,192 --> 00:18:32,277
who may be working with General Carillo.

319
00:18:33,403 --> 00:18:34,863
They're Dionisio and Manalo.

320
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:38,033
Who among them
do you think is hiding something?

321
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:40,452
General Manalo, sir.

322
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:43,622
[Marcus] <i>His eyes move around a lot.</i>

323
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:45,124
<i>He can't look directly at us.</i>

324
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:47,668
And Colonel Dionisio…

325
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,586
<i>He was too defensive.</i>

326
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:52,005
Me too.

327
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:54,508
I created an evidence board.

328
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:59,346
Solares and Madrigal.

329
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:01,431
They worked with General Carillo

330
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:04,268
in organizing the security
for the investment summit.

331
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:08,355
[foreboding music playing]

332
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:27,124
Right from the start,

333
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:29,251
they've been with General Carillo.

334
00:19:32,504 --> 00:19:34,381
General Carillo is too good.

335
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:38,010
But when it comes to his henchmen…

336
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,804
we may be able to get something.

337
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:47,936
Domingo's one of them too?

338
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,323
[rapid gunshots]

339
00:19:59,406 --> 00:20:01,158
[Marcus] This is an ambush!
Hold your fire!

340
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,367
What are you doing?!

341
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,871
Innocent people will die
because of what you're doing!

342
00:20:05,954 --> 00:20:08,207
- [gunshots]
- [groans]

343
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:09,625
- [Marcus] That's enough!
- [Lara] Stand down.

344
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:11,168
Don't shoot him!

345
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:16,131
[foreboding music continues]

346
00:20:29,978 --> 00:20:35,400
[foreboding music continues]

347
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:37,778
I've had my suspicions on him
for a while now.

348
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:38,737
He's a loose cannon.

349
00:20:38,820 --> 00:20:40,822
I can't trust him anymore, Lara.

350
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:43,200
We don't know
if he was telling the truth that

351
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:44,701
he just defended himself.

352
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:46,203
You and the team.

353
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:48,789
We have to give him another chance.

354
00:20:48,872 --> 00:20:52,417
Lara just forced me
to give him another chance.

355
00:20:53,585 --> 00:20:56,421
[doorknob rattling]

356
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,924
[beeping]

357
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:02,094
[foreboding music continues]

358
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:04,304
[Azuelo] Domingo.

359
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:05,764
[Felix] Director Azuelo.

360
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:08,141
What's going on?

361
00:21:09,017 --> 00:21:10,602
What are you doing here?

362
00:21:11,186 --> 00:21:12,479
Is there a briefing?

363
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,774
- Where's the TFA?
- [Azuelo] They're not here.

364
00:21:15,857 --> 00:21:18,110
We were just talking about something.

365
00:21:18,819 --> 00:21:20,112
Ahh.

366
00:21:20,988 --> 00:21:24,241
I understand that Espina
and Marcus are here.

367
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:27,536
But Sabdani?

368
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:30,330
[Felix] Well, sir.

369
00:21:30,414 --> 00:21:32,291
How about me? Why wasn't I included here?

370
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:36,420
[suspenseful music playing]

371
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:37,629
Okay.

372
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:39,047
Fine. Bye.

373
00:21:48,015 --> 00:21:49,182
[door closes]

374
00:21:51,518 --> 00:21:57,858
[suspenseful music continues]

375
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:19,421
[suspenseful music continues]

376
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:40,901
[suspenseful music continues]

377
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:51,036
What will happen to you now?

378
00:22:51,119 --> 00:22:52,537
Sir Mustapha is now gone.

379
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:53,997
- They can--
- I'll be fine.

380
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:56,208
Before they find out who I really am,

381
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:57,334
I won't be here anymore.

382
00:22:57,417 --> 00:22:59,252
Why don't you just tell Marcus?

383
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:01,129
I know him. He'll understand you.

384
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,047
He will support you.

385
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:04,841
He can't know who I really am.

386
00:23:06,009 --> 00:23:09,221
If this blows up,
he might get dragged too. It's risky.

387
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:11,014
Sir Mustapha is no longer here

388
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:13,183
to prove who I really am.

389
00:23:13,266 --> 00:23:14,601
But…

390
00:23:14,684 --> 00:23:15,685
[Jalil] We can't tell him!

391
00:23:15,769 --> 00:23:18,980
If my identity gets revealed,
only I should go down for it

392
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:21,691
so that we can continue what we're doing.

393
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:23,860
He can't get dragged in it.

394
00:23:23,944 --> 00:23:27,322
[tense music playing]

395
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:43,463
There's a snake in our grass.

396
00:23:44,047 --> 00:23:50,470
[man] <i>We need to purge the traitor</i>
<i>in our own ranks.</i>

397
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:53,515
[Teresa] <i>Allan's bandage is missing.</i>

398
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:56,434
I wanted to get its DNA tested.

399
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:58,270
Allan might be Gabriel.

400
00:23:58,353 --> 00:24:00,480
[man]
You already know who to deliver those to.

401
00:24:00,564 --> 00:24:01,898
[man] <i>Yes, General.</i>

402
00:24:03,483 --> 00:24:06,570
[Azuelo]
<i>Reyes is going after General Madrigal</i>

403
00:24:06,653 --> 00:24:09,781
who is sending suitcases with money.

404
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,703
Cuchy?

405
00:24:15,495 --> 00:24:16,955
Is someone in there?

406
00:24:20,792 --> 00:24:25,046
[theme music playing]

407
00:24:28,383 --> 00:24:30,051
‪-[blows, kicks landing]
‪-[grunts] Argh!
